        <p> Upon request, he informed us that first we head for the Chocolate Hills because they are the most away. The journey should last almost 1.5 hours and led past many beautiful rice fields, where some of them even worked with water buffalos. Unfortunately, there were no holding options in exactly these places, so that we could not capture anything. There were still tons of rice fields and this time we could even hold. The driver even wanted to keep the men and women from work so that we could take pictures, but we thankfully rejected this. At some point the street led us past a lake and in the end the driver stopped and showed us the "Parlar Staudamm". We walked across the street and of course took pictures. The dam seemed to shine golden and the driver told me that this lake or the adjacent river supplies the entire fields further north. </p>
    </div>
